description.narrative: The development objective is to increase access to land information services by all stakeholders through development of an improved land administration system in selected provinces of Vietnam. This objective will be achieved through ensuring that land users, including businesses and households, have access to more efficient, reliable, and transparent services from land administration services.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I. 4.(d) | Description :Adopt revised land registration service standards acceptable to theAssociation | Due Date :30-Jun-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I. 4.(e) | Description :Design & install a national land data warehouse, in a mannersatisfactory to the Association | Due Date :31-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section II. A.(b) | Description :Semi-annual progress reports furnished to IDA by Jan 15 & Jun 15each year, beginning Jan 15, 2009. | Frequency :Quarterly

title.narrative: Component 2: Number of commune public awareness plans implemented

comment.narrative: This requires some evaluation by the LRO/PPMU. It must be a media campaign that extends beyond simply holding public meetings

title.narrative: Number of individuals or households granted with LURCs under the project

comment.narrative: Individual or household may granted few LURCs for different land parcel but it will only count as one.

title.narrative: Number of LURCs distributed being registered with name of women land users

comment.narrative: Land Law requires both names to be recorded on the certificate if jointly owned. The statistics can be collected for all new TScontracts. LROs should collect these data at the time of profile approval. Accordingly this covers: (i) LURCs only in the name of awoman (ii) LURCs in the name of husband and wife.
Number of profile that updated and approved by commune PC and district LRO.

title.narrative: Number of Land Registration Offices modernized and operational

comment.narrative: This includes Province and district LROs in the province where modern computer equipment has been installed, VILIS and the networkis used to register applications by land users

title.narrative: Number of communes operationally connected to land information system

comment.narrative: This includes communes in the province that have PCs and can now access the database by internet or cable.

title.narrative: Land area granted with LURCs under the project

comment.narrative: This indicator should be collected during LURC issuance process
